The paper discusses a machine learning approach for generating interpretable control strategies using fuzzy controllers. The approach involves using genetic programming and reinforcement learning to automatically adjust the controller parameters and select relevant state features. This falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
